The paper deals with the classic cake-cutting problem, which is a well-known problem in computational social choice theory (cs.GT). The problem involves partitioning a cake among agents, which requires the use of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper proposes an improved algorithm for solving the problem, which involves incorporating new insights and simplifying several steps, indicating the use of artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI). The paper also involves mathematical analysis and optimization, which falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper deals with the concept of fairness, which is a central theme in computational complexity theory (cs.CC).
